=========================================
C++ std::pair - INTERVIEW NOTES
=========================================

1. What is pair?
----------------
std::pair is a container in STL that stores TWO values (can be different types).

Defined in:
#include <utility>

Example:
pair<int, string>

-----------------------------------------

2. Structure
-------------
A pair has two members:

first  -> first value
second -> second value

Example:
pair<int,string> p = {1,"A"};

p.first  = 1
p.second = "A"

-----------------------------------------

3. Ways to create pair
----------------------

pair<int,int> p1;                 // default
pair<int,int> p2(1,2);            // constructor
pair<int,int> p3 = {1,2};         // uniform init
auto p4 = make_pair(1,2);         // make_pair

-----------------------------------------

4. make_pair()
--------------
Used to create pair without specifying type.

auto p = make_pair(10, "Hello");

-----------------------------------------

5. tie() function
-----------------
Used to unpack pair values into variables.

pair<int,int> p = {1,2};

int a,b;
tie(a,b) = p;

Ignore second value:

tie(a, ignore) = p;

-----------------------------------------

6. Key Features
---------------
✓ Stores 2 values
✓ Can be different types
✓ Simple struct-like container
✓ Used in maps, algorithms

-----------------------------------------

7. Common Use Cases
-------------------
✓ map stores (key, value)
✓ returning 2 values from function
✓ sorting pairs
✓ adjacency lists in graphs

Example:
vector<pair<int,int>> v;

-----------------------------------------

8. Sorting pairs
----------------
By default:
sort by first, then second

Example:
{1,5} < {1,7} < {2,1}

